MedConnect Doctor-Patient Portal

Overview
This repo contains the MedConnect government medical portal (React + Vite frontend, Node + MongoDB backend).
It includes patient and doctor dashboards, services, research registry views, and seeded mock data.

Quick Start
1) Install dependencies: npm install
2) Start API server:
   - Set MONGODB_URI to your Mongo connection string (example: mongodb://localhost:27017)
   - Run: npm run server
3) Start the frontend: npm run dev
4) Open the app at http://localhost:5173

Build
npm run build

Environment
MONGODB_URI is required for the API server.

Mock Accounts
Doctor: doctor@test.com / Welcome123!
Patient: alex@test.com / Welcome123!

Notes
The seed includes multiple doctors, patients, appointments, lab reports, pharmacy orders, diagnostic tests,
health packages, blood bank inventory, claims, trials, and guidelines.
